			<script>--[[
Likely the basic answers you want on triggers are at:
  https://wiki.mudlet.org/w/Manual:Trigger_Engine
  Regex cheat sheet: https://www.rexegg.com/regex-quickstart.html
  
IMPORTANT all player triggers are disabled by default. We do this to not check for uneeded triggers.
If you need a trigger to run make certain to double click it. When you do a check will appear in the 
box to the left of the trigger.
As you run Parthia updates new triggers may automatically populate.
  
In short with a trigger: you tell mudlet when xyz text is sent to the player from the server do this code.
We created some triggers to get you started, they are in Your_Triggers/Game Events

Parthia is intended to be a community project.
As we wrote code we made certain to comment nearly every line.
There will be many examples to reference in TEC_Client_Triggers.

Any code written in the Your_Triggers folder will never be removed by Pathia updates.
We highly recommend backing up all the Your_ files in your `The Eternal City` mudlet profile.
You could do this by:
  selecting the folder, and click export at the top of the page
  right clicking the folder, select copy than paste that data into a text editor

We are happy to answer questions.
Parthia's discord server is: https://discord.gg/QGztVx
Our github page is: https://github.com/TheEternalCitizens/mudlet-integration

Another wonderful source of answers and knowledge is:
Mudlet's discord server: https://discord.gg/FfkEx7
mudlet manual: https://wiki.mudlet.org/w/Manual:Contents
mudlet function reference: https://wiki.mudlet.org/w/Manual:Lua_Functions
  ^This is not a complete list but it is a wonderful start^
  
Good lua references:
https://www.lua.org/pil/contents.html
https://docs.coronalabs.com/api/index.html --Good for if you already know the basics.

As you write code you can share it at the parthia discord server on the player-scripts channel.
]]--</script>
